Chocolate Comparison ğŸ«ğŸ«ğŸ«
.
. 
So this one is probably gonna be a little shocker to some. And as with everything, this is all very goal dependentğŸ‘ŒBut sometimes the 'healthier' option is not the best option to suit your goals. But let me put that into a little more context ğŸ¤”
.
.
So I'm sure most of you have been lead to believe dark chocolate is 'better' for you. It is full of antioxidants, good fats and has been linked to many health benefits. But if you ABSOLUTELY hate it and are forcing yourself to eat it so you can have a treat, is it really healthy? To an extent, we should be eating foods that are more nutritious but your treats should also feel like a treat? Who's with me on that one? ğŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸
.
.
So the above photo shows a milkybar wowsome which has less calories, less sugar, less fat and practically identical protein to dark chocolate. So if your goal is weight loss the milkybar is actually probably the better option. Now if your goal is healthy eating, the dark chocolate definitely wins ğŸ‰
.
.
Again it all is really goal dependent. I eat both. I like both. But my goals may not be the same as yours. I am not saying one is better for you than the other I am simply saying, make an informed choice when picking a 'treat' and please don't force feed yourself dark chocolate just because its 'healthier'. ğŸ™ˆğŸ™ˆğŸ™ˆ
P. S please don't take this out of context and start eating crap food because it is lower calorieğŸ˜•

caption:
ğŸ¦„Have a slow metabolism? What are you doing about it?
.
.
ğŸ’So first things first, unless you have a hormonal imbalance which has been diagnosed chances are you don't have a anything wrong with your Basal Metabolic Rate. If you THINK you have a 'slow' metabolism it's probably because you don't look after your dietary intake and you have a sedentary lifestyle!!! ğŸ™ˆğŸ™ˆğŸ™ˆ
.
.
ğŸ¦People want to use excusesğŸ¤¦â€â™€ï¸Some people genuinely have difficult circumstances to overcome and others are just full Ã³f BS ğŸ˜‘ğŸ˜‘ğŸ˜‘
.
.
ğŸ°I often get asked how do I have such a 'fast' metabolism, especially because I eat so much. Well my BMR is based on the fact that I have ALWAYS been active and in the last 5 years I have dramatically improved my eating habits. But it took 5 years, not 5 days or 5 weeks, 5 yearsğŸ‘†ğŸ‘†
.
.
ğŸ¦„Don't think after 6 weeks of exercise you are going to dramatically overhaul the years of lack of exercise. Changing from a takeaway at lunch to a salad for a week, will not correct all the damage to your hormonal system. It takes time to correct the damage you have done to your body. And unfortunately that is what it is. Lack of exercise and immobility is damage. Excessive body fat and lack of muscle mass is damage. In a lot of cases, it is also malnourishment.
.
.
ğŸ’But you CAN change it. It won't happen in a week. It won't happen in a month. It may even take longer than a year. But you can improve it. Step by step. Day by day. Working on a lifestyle that is sustainable. A way of living that is healthy but not too restrictive. caption:
Lovely little find in @aldi_ireland ğŸ˜ŠğŸ˜ŠğŸ˜Š .
.
I've said it before and I'll say it again, eating healthy does not have to be boringğŸš«ğŸš«ğŸš«. If you hate plain rice, don't eat it. Opt for the more interesting style and get some veggies in while you're at it ğŸ‘Œ Now I actually like plain rice and this is a rare treat to me (because I rarely get a chance to eat warm food and this is a steam pack ğŸ˜­).
.
.
The best diet out there is the one YOU can stick to. If you can't stick to it, you're going nowhere. Now sometimes you may go hell for leather with an event coming up like holidays or a wedding etc (that's different). If you are constantly eating clean for 6 weeks and binging for the other 46 you have not found a sustainable way of living ğŸ˜‘ğŸ˜‘ğŸ˜‘
.
.
If you are unsure of what you should be doing to achieve your goals. Speak to a nutritionist or dietician ğŸ‘

#healthylifestyle #healthyliving #healthyalternative #fitlife #fitlifestyle #fitliving #balancedlifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitchick #fitgirls #fitfam #irishfitfam

Are you the type of person that doesn't like a food before you've even tried it? Eating with your eyes rather than your mouth? You've a list of dislikes longer than your list of likesğŸ™„ğŸ¤”
.
.
I used to be you ğŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸ğŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸ğŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸ Genuinely I was the pickiest person going. Now I'm still a bit weird with some things touching each other on a plate and I'm never going to be a cauliflower fan but I've changed DRAMATICALLY. Why? Well to be totally honest I just grew up. I know it's hard for some to hear but that's exactly what it is. ğŸ™ˆ Now obviously intolerances are a totally different kettle of fish ğŸ¤ª But if you are just choosing to eat broccoli as your only veg, fish doesn't exist in your diet and potatoes are your only starch and it's purely down to not trying other foods, you really need to broaden your horizonsğŸ‘Š
.
.
You are missing out on so much nutrients and whole foods by keeping your diet so limited. You won't like them all. That's understandable but at least try ğŸ‘
.
.
P. S up until recently I couldn't stand Goats cheese but because I eat very little meat I had to start finding higher protein alternatives. After a few tries I'm a fan ğŸ‘†

caption: Since I started following a Pescatarian diet I have Tuna every single day ğŸŸğŸŸ It may be as a snack or in a salad. This week I put it in an egg bake for breakfastğŸ³ğŸ³ Protein is an essential part of all diets no matter your goals ğŸ’ªğŸ‘ŒBut I especially need it this week for recovery in the run up to our Connacht Final ğŸ’™ğŸ’› Thanks @johnwestire for hitting me up ğŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸ğŸ˜ #NaturalProteinPitstop #GetTheBestOutOfJohnWest

Health versus Calorie Control explained ğŸ™„

This is a big topic for me. As a nutritionist, health is priority. Whatever nourishes your body will be what I advise. Food is fuel â›½

Counting calories is constantly thrown all over my news feed. Flexible dieting and IIFYM. The list goes on.... ğŸ˜‘ğŸ˜‘ğŸ˜‘ 1. So firstly, yes a calorie is a calorie. But the problem with some of these posts is, people see calorie for calorie comparisons, substitute foods based on these calorie comparisons but don't understand anything about their own caloric intake. I've seen doughnuts compared to wholefood bars, Alcohol compared to smoothies etc. People see 'fitness people' eating these foods so eat them themselves, uneducated to the fact that they may be in a calorie surplus while the said educator was probably eating this in a calorie deficit. Understand it is overall calories that count and each individual is different. Calorie intake is based on weight, height, age, gender, activity level, etc.
.
. 
2. While a calorie is a calorie. Micros count!!!!!! Eating a Mc Donald's every morning may 'Fit your macros' but my god are you missing out on the fibre, magnesium, Iron, Zinc, and B Group Vitamins that a big bowl of oats provide ğŸ¥£ğŸ¥£ğŸ¥£
.
. 
3. Gastrointestinal discomfort. I have a sensitive stomach so this MAY be just me but my God do I feel like crap after a takeaway/chocolate binge. Its fine every once in awhile but consistently is just hard ğŸ˜± Even if the calories were the same, I'd take my fish and greens any dayğŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸
.
. 
4. From my experience and experience with other athletes, wholefoods improve performance. If you asked me to go play a game tomorrow under 2 different conditions 1. 2000 Cals of wholefoods, lots of complex carbs, healthy fats, protein and water versus 2. 2000 Cals of Chips, pizza and diet coke. I can tell you now which one I'd feel better on ğŸ¤ªğŸ¤ªğŸ¤ª
.
.
So yes, a calorie is a calorie and calorie wise there is no difference between water and diet coke. And with regards Aspartame do your research. Again, it all comes back to goals. I certainly wouldn't be able to fuel my body with crap and perform well, another may be able but at least be educated next time ğŸ¤Ÿ

caption:
'Elephants never forget' ğŸ˜ğŸ˜ğŸ˜ To all the people out there spending Father's Day with their Dad's, spoil them ğŸ’œ To those who have lost theirs but are lucky enough to have made memories, treasure them ğŸ’œ

#happyfathersday #thebestmemories #daddysgirl

But #balance ğŸ˜‹ğŸ˜‹ğŸ˜‹ I use this hash tag a lot and I'm a true believer in it. But it is all very relative. People throw it around A LOT and the problem is it ends up becoming an imbalance ğŸ™ˆ

Remember to never lose sight of your goals ğŸ‘†They are key. They are drivers. ğŸ‘†If your goal is weight loss and you are 'treating' yo self after every good thing you do, chances are you may be 'balanced' but only on the scales because you have cancelled out any deficit you were previously in ğŸ˜« But its not all about weight loss. I consider balance being able to go out with friends on social occasions for a meal or a few drinks. But I would not be able to do this every weekend with my lifestyle ğŸ™„ğŸ˜´ That to me would be an imbalance âŒâŒâŒ I am not saying its all about deprivation. Far from it ğŸ¤Ÿ Treating yourself is NECESSARY. But is it really a treat when it's happening regularly. I'm all for the YOLO but binge drinking every weekend and expecting fat loss is difficult (not impossible but really f*cking hardğŸ¤ª) Whatever you do, take ownership for it ğŸ‘ŠGoals are not easy to achieve but it depends on the effort you put in too. Minimal effort = Minimal results ğŸ˜±

Fast forward to pic 2. I'm just home from a weekend of ğŸ¥‚ and ğŸ«. I've been carrying injuries so I haven't been as consistent with training but I still eat really well ğŸ‘†

Life is not about being ripped 24/7. Life is about memories. Life is about experiences. Life is about spending time with loved ones. Life is not about guilt over a pizza slice or running miles to burn off a glass of wine.

caption:
Pet Peave alert âš ï¸âš ï¸âš ï¸
.
.
.
The odd person gives me the 'you don't know what it's like, you've never been overweight' OR 'sure you've always been fit, you wouldn't understand'. There are so many points I can make to this comment ğŸ˜¡ğŸ˜¡ğŸ˜¡
.
.
.
1. I may not have ever been over weight because health and fitness have always been a huge part of my life so no weight is something I never struggled with. And the reason I am fit is because I work for it. Not because I am NATURALLY fit. Not because fitness comes easy to me but because I push myself, every day ğŸ‘ŠğŸ‘ŠğŸ‘Š
.
.
.
2. Body Confidence is a whole different kettle of fish and this is something I can relate to. Being a certain clothes size or having a low body fat % does NOT equate to being happy. I have been 8 stone, a size 6 and seriously unhappy. Like most women I struggled with self image. I would not leave the house without make up. If I ever had to buy clothes in more than an 8 I considered myself fat ğŸ™ŠğŸ˜©ğŸ˜­ Do not think just because someone is slim that they are happy or confident because the 2 just do not go hand in hand ğŸ™„ğŸ™„. .
.
.
3. And no I've never had to lose weight but dya know what I did have to gain weight. 2 stone to be precise. Mostly muscle, a little fat. Not everyone's journey is the same. Sometimes it's just as important to gain weight as it is to lose it. But truth be told I am the happiest I have ever been with my body ğŸ˜ I fuel it well. I eat LOADS, mostly nutritious wholefoods, the odd time junk food ğŸ¤— I train hard, I am strong, I am fit and I am fast. I don't wear make up every day but I feel a million dollars when I do. I have crazy wild curls that I have finally learned to love. I have days that I think I'm fat, days I think I'm too muscly (it's called being a woman ğŸ˜‚) but all in all I'm happy ğŸ’–

Next time you think about saying something to someone think about what you are saying. Is it beneficial to the person? Is it a nice thing to say? Is it necessary?

Remember, if you have nothing nice to say. Don't say it at all ğŸ˜‘

Top tips for eating on the go ğŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸ğŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸ğŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸ Most days I'm gone from 5-22 so I understand how important it is to have good options on the go. I tend to bring all my food with me but sometimes I need to buy out ğŸ™Š

1. The best you will be prepared is when you make the food yourself. Knowing exactly what is going into your food. This is key but more often than not we end up having to buy out. Thankfully there are so many healthy options these days ğŸ˜ğŸ‘Œ 2. Structure your meal around protein. If it is from a salad counter pick a good quality meat/fish, tins of tuna are great, these tuna packs from @johnwestire taste AWESOME ğŸ˜ You may find a protein shake handy or even some Greek yogurt
Protein rich foods keep us fuller for longer and have a higher thermic effect from food. No matter what your goals are having a diet high in protein will be beneficial regardless ğŸ‘Œ

3. Try not to go for seriously long periods without food as we tend to get over hungry and pick the worst options I. Ã‰ takeaways and junk food

4. Be careful of certain 'health foods' as their sugar content is often through the roof ğŸ™ˆ Choose snacks like nuts, seeds, yogurt, fruit and veggies ğŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸ There are now so many healthy convenience foods that there is really never any excuse to eat badly on the go ğŸ‘ŒğŸ‘ŒğŸ‘Œ #healthylifestyle #healthyeatingonthego #balancedlifestyle #healthyliving #fitliving #fitlifestyle #eatforhealth #eatforperformance #fitgirl #fitchick #fitfam #irishfitfam

While I can't say I'll ever be the person to relax 100% I'm certainly not the stressed out Sheila I used to be ğŸ™ˆ I have learned to enjoy my time off. I have seen more places and made more memories in the last 2 and a half years than I have in my entire life (no joke) ğŸ˜²ğŸ˜²ğŸ˜² I have ticked bucket list adventures off. I have spent time with friends and family â¤ï¸ And it's only May yet ğŸ˜‰ğŸ˜ğŸŒ Still lots more to come.

I've also changed my mindset. I used to want to be a certain body fat. Or hit a certain amount of pull ups. Chasing abs. My ideals have changed so much.
My mindset now: I have fat but not that much. I can do a pull up, go mÃ©. I may not have a 6 pack but dya know what I've good legs. Confidence (not Cockiness) is the most amazing trait. Embrace it ğŸ’“

What is health??? Some will say a 'normal' BMI, others will say a good diet, exercise daily, don't smoke, no alcohol, being free from disease.

Others get more in depth. You need to see visible abs in order to be a healthy weight. Or you need to train until you feel like collapsing. High cÃ¡rb/low fat or low cÃ¡rb/high fat. Green tea. Green shakes. Kale. Chia seeds. More weights. More cardio.

My idea of health:
ğŸ‘‰ THAT EAR TO EAR SMILE ğŸ˜ğŸ˜ğŸ˜
ğŸ‘‰ Seeing my sister for the first time in 18 months and being ABLE to go to visit her and take the holiday of a lifetime because I am fit and able
ğŸ‘‰ Having a beer in my hand because dya know what? I was on holidays and I bloody well deserved a beer
ğŸ‘‰ Being happy and confident in my body. Not worrying that my bottoms were too small and I had rolls
ğŸ‘‰ ENJOYING my life. Nourishing my body but eating out if I want it. Exercising because I love it and appreciate how lucky I am to be able â¤ï¸ Everyone's idea of health is different. Health to me is not:
âŒ Starving yourself to achieve the perfect body. Nobody is perfect. Embrace your flaws.
âŒ Exercising as punishment
âŒ Missing out on life
âŒ Running down people's lifestyle choices. If you want to go out every weekend, your choice. If you don't want to drink or smoke, also your choice.

Happy Friday peepsâ¤ï¸â¤ï¸â¤ï¸ #throwback #happiness #smiles #happy #dowhatmakesyouhappy #healthylifestyle #health #healthyliving #fitliving #fitlife #fitlifestyle #fitgirls #fitchick #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Morning guys ğŸ¤—

So here are some of the snacks I've had this week ğŸ˜ I just want to explain to you the difference between healthy foods and calorie control ğŸ‘Œ

This is all very goal dependent but you CAN over consume healthy foods. Healthy foods contain calories too and if your calories in are higher than your calories out even though you are eating super healthy you can still gain weight ğŸ˜¬ğŸ™„ This picture is 2 different snacks I ate during the week. Both were scrumptious ğŸ¤©ğŸ˜ But the 'healthier' option was double the calories of the alternative. Am I saying don't eat the raw bar? No, absolutely not but be mindful that just because its healthier doesn't mean its lower in calories. My goal is weight maintenance and health. So a little of the healthy stuff is perfect for me with a little fibre one bar here and there because.... Balance ğŸ‘Œâ¤ï¸ Tag a friend ğŸ‘ŒğŸ™Œ #healthylifestyle #health #healthyliving #balance #balancedlifestyle #beeducated #fitlife #fitliving #fitfam #fitgirls #irishfitfam

Weight loss or weight maintenance is relatively simple. Overall weekly calories in are less than calories out. ğŸ¤—ğŸ˜„ It is that simple. Unfortunately people like to overcomplicate situations ğŸ™„ğŸ¤ So Monday to Friday you have cut out bread, dairy, refined sugars, processed foods. The worst thing to touch your lips is a protein bar or piece of fruit. Then the weekend comes and you're out on the lash, takeaway the following day washed down with a coke. Sound familiar?

Guys, you are kidding yourselves ğŸ˜µğŸ˜µI am not saying you can never go out or have takeaways but weekends count. They are not a free for all. They account for almost 30% of your week ğŸ™ˆ 
Stop over analysing it.
ğŸ‘‰ Eat well Monday - Sunday
ğŸ‘‰ Enjoy your treats but keep goals in mind
ğŸ‘‰ Move daily
ğŸ‘‰ Alcohol in moderation
ğŸ‘‰ Drink at least 2 litres of water a day

It's not easy but it is simple. Find what suits you ğŸ˜„

caption:
ğŸ‘‰How to improve pull ups

Firstly, understand pull ups/chin ups are hard. It is not a case of 'Oh I started going to the gym I should now be able to do a pull up' âŒâŒâŒ I am sharing a few tips that have helped me through the years. And notice that word 'years' because that is how long it took me ğŸ˜±ğŸ™ˆ ğŸ‘‰You need a strong back. Back and biceps are the primary muscles used in this exercise. A strong back is built through exercises like Deadlifts, Rack Pulls, Rows, Pull Downs etc. And go heavy (with correct form and technique of course). ğŸ‘‰ Your body weight and body fat will have an impact. The heavier you are, the heavier you have to lift. The more excess body fat you have, the harder you are to lift. But this does not mean the lighter you are the easier you are to lift. I was once 8 and half stone and could barely bend my elbows left alone pull myself up ğŸ˜…ğŸ˜…ğŸ˜…You need to have a balance of both. Low body fat and strength ğŸ‘Œ ğŸ‘‰Slow eccentrics - jump to the top of the bar and slowly lower yourself down. And repeat. Often. ğŸ‘‰ Ever heard practice makes perfect ğŸ‘ŒIt definitely applies here. Practice often. You want to get better at something? Once a week is not enough!!!! Happy to hear other tips if anyone wants to let us know how they improved? â¤ï¸ #chinups #Rackpulls #strongback #strongirls #strongwomen #strong #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitgirl #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Lacking consistency = Lacking results ğŸ‘Š

Like it or not, it's the truth ğŸ™ˆ Are you the type to work seriously hard for a week only to have a few drinks at the weekend which leads you to missing your Monday workout? Or maybe it's a month of hard work and expecting to see instant results!? Sound familiar ğŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸ğŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸ğŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸ If that's the way you want to live your life, setting yourself up for disappointment that's fine. But stop blaming everything else and start looking at the real reason you are not getting results â˜ï¸â˜ï¸â˜ï¸ My own personal example. On holidays I drank A lot, ate totally off course and exercised once every 2/3 days. Lack of consistency lead to a very bloated, swelled Amanda. I came home, Ate really well, trained every day and then Easter weekend came = chocolate and gin. Result: Same bloated AmandağŸ¡ğŸ¡ğŸ¡ Finally the last 2 weeks I have been CONSISTENT. NO ALCOHOL. Back to training 5-6 times a week. Eating well and I eventually feel kinda back to normal ğŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸ğŸ˜ Don't expect to see results for a half hearted effort. It just does not work that way ğŸ‘ ~ You have to make a change to see a change ~

caption:
I'm back ğŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸ğŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸ğŸ™‹â€â™€ï¸ This week I am trying to beat the holiday and bank holiday bloat ğŸ¡ğŸ¡ğŸ¡ I'm sure I'm not the only one that over indulged but if you're like me you probably felt absolutely CRAP afterwards ğŸ™ˆğŸ™ŠSo this week is beat the bloat week for me ğŸ‘ŠğŸ‘Š How am I trying to reduce the swell?
ğŸ‘‰Drink 3-4L water daily
ğŸ‘‰ Combo of field training and weights (just get moving daily)
ğŸ‘‰ This week I've decided to take meat from my diet

Let me elaborate. I am not a plant based enthusiast and I am not a meat hater. I don't believe in extremism and this is my opinion so please for those of you who feel the need to go to town on this post, don't. I am simply voicing my opinion and giving my reasons. I don't believe meat causes cancer. Cancer is multi factorial and it is very easy to blame cancer on 1 thing. What about air pollution? What about the tap water we drink? Daily stresses in people's lives? Financial worries? Genetics? Similarly, I don't believe in veganism. I believe if you HAVE TO supplement a diet, it is not substantial. Again, OPINION!!! Why have I decided meat free this week?

1. Meat is hard tÃ³ digest. It requires a lot of work by enzymes and makes our gut work harder. My poor gut has had a tough time of it recently so I'm trying to give it a break â¤ï¸
2. Due to mass production, the quality of all food has gone to ğŸ’© (not just meat, plant based foods too,) Unfortunately, meat has been hit one of the worst. So for me, it is absolutely no harm taking a break from that.
3. I can increase micros. Although I don't believe in pure plant based, it is so important to get a good daily dose of fruits and veggies
4. Fish is an excellent source of protein, I feel satisfied and I don't feel I have taken anything away from my diet nutritionallyğŸ¤—ğŸ¤—ğŸ¤— Anybody else out there try something like this or is pescatarian? Real Talk ğŸ¤ªğŸ¤ªğŸ¤ª I have been really struggling to beat the bloat this week after holidays. I am back to regular eating habits, drinking at least 3 litres of water and today has been my first rest day. Yet, I feel sluggish and lethargic and it was really getting me down until today.

Today, I read a blog post from a young girl who was taken way before her time. The post really resignated with me. Here I am complaining that I can't see my abs anymore while others out there are dying. Life is way too short to be knit picking over silly little things. I know first hand how fast a life can be taken away and moaning about tiny insignificant details is absolutely absurd âŒâŒâŒâŒ So I am going to make the most of my weekendâ¤ï¸ I am catching up with friends, playing a match, enjoying a night out or 2ğŸ˜‰ and coaching at my first ever championship game with the u14 team I am involved with. I will eat like normal with  a little Easter egg here and thereğŸ˜‰ And I'll stop worrying about the silly stupid irrelevant things ğŸ¤—

ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ And not 2 f*#ks given. I'm 1/3 alcohol, 1/3 sugar and 1/3 water., cause ya know... Balance ğŸ˜‚ Pictures or words cannot describe the incredible holiday I've had. It was a mental and physical rest from everything in life and it was just amazing ğŸ˜Seeing my sister again was the icing on the ğŸ‚but we literally should not be allowed let out together ğŸ˜‚ğŸ™ˆ Normality resumed yesterday when I returned to a training game after 36 hours of no sleep and just a couple of hours off the plane ğŸ¤£ I also weaned my way back into healthy eating and enjoyed a 15 hour sleep last nightğŸ˜´

caption:
This will be on my gravestone the amount of times I've said this and my friends are sick of hearing it. But if it helps one young person stay in sport I would be happy ğŸ’“
.
.
When I was younger I put my hand up for everything (quote from my DadğŸ¤£). Athletics, Badminton, Cross country,  Draughts, Egg and spoon race I'd say I could do the alphabet of what I tried ğŸ™ˆ And I was absolutely CRAP at every single one of them ğŸ™ˆğŸ¤£ Like really crap. And to make matters worse, my sister was a little superstar. She had an all Ireland medal at 7, she played football with the boys she was just super talented ğŸ˜ Still is ğŸ’“ 
I never started on any team, I was always picked last. One time, I actually had to give my football boots to another player because she forgot hers (this other player was no superstar either, I was just that poor). The one thing I did have was a good attitude, a great one actually. I never let it get me down. I always still kept with it, probably more for the social side to be honest ğŸ˜‚ğŸ™ˆ .
.
But I kept with it. Even though I was hopeless. I kept training. Then I trained harder. Then I trained harder than everyone else. Then I became fit, fitter than a lot of people. Then, I started going to the gym and I became stronger. Stronger than most. .
.
So now, with a good attitude and a decent level of fitness. I started to make All Ireland winning schools teams, Roscommon panels, UCD O Connor panels and last year made my first ever Connaught panel ğŸ¤—ğŸ˜ I still have a fear of the goals and my overhead catch is crap but I'm an athlete. What I always wanted to be. Never give up on something because of the hard work it will take to get there, the time will pass anyway ğŸ‘Œ
.
.
Hard Work beats talent, when talent doesn't work hard ğŸ‘ŠğŸ‘ŠğŸ‘Š
.
.
P.s I'm not chickening out on my video instas I will have one very soon ğŸ˜‰
.
.

caption:
Ok this week is Amanda is mean week ğŸ™ˆ

I'm going to hit you with a few home truths. ğŸ™ˆğŸ™ˆğŸ™ˆ People take it easy on themselves. People use excuses. People take short cuts. People have no patience. People reward themselves far too easily âŒâŒâŒ If you want a change, you need to make a change. It will take sacrifice. Sacrifice isn't easy. ğŸ‘Š

Scenario 1: You want to lose weight. But you're not making any sacrifices = you will get nowhere. It doesn't have to something crazy like go gluten free or vegan. Something as simple as removing your 11 o clock chocolate break daily will lead to results ğŸ˜ You NEED to make a sacrifice to reap the rewards. If you keep doing qhat you've always done, you'll keep getting what you always got ğŸ™ˆThe truth hurts ğŸ‘Š

Scenario 2: You want to get fitter, stronger, leaner. But you're just not putting in the effort. It's not easy being fit. You don't just wake up lean (unless you are one of the lucky ones or are u18). Strength doesn't grow on trees. You need to work at it. You need to consistently fight for it. 
In anything you do, unless you make a sacrifice you will not see results ğŸ™ˆ

My own fitness story: I worked at it. I made myself sick once from training so hard. Then I decided to nourish my body. As soon as I did that I started to see results- performance and aesthetic wise. It wasn't easy. Ever. But I'm driven and I have goals to achieve. I'm not an excuse maker. I start most of my days at 5am and finish close to 10pm but I make it work. Because my health is my driver. Health is more important to me than excuses ğŸ‘ŠğŸ‘ğŸ˜ #sacrifice #hardwork #workhard #playhard #fitliving #fitlifestyle #fitchick #fuelforperformance #fuelyourself #healthyliving #fitfam #irishfitfam

caption:
Let's talk food consumption ğŸ¥ğŸ¥‘
.
.
Ok, so this is a really important post and I need you all to listen up.
.
.
In order to understand what you need to eat and why, in order to eat for your goals, in order to get optimal body composition, in order to get the best from your body performance wise, you need to stop looking up the foods people eat and invest in a nutrition plan/nutritionist/coach etc.
.
.
Why?
- Firstly, every single one of you are different. So why would you all eat the same? Everyone has different schedules. Everyone has different training plans. You are all different weights and heights so why would you all eat the same. Social media is RIDICULOUS at times comparing whole nutritious foods to fast foods just because they are the same calories. People who are not as knowledgable will see this and think 'oh it's ok then to have fast food all the time because it's the same calories' ğŸ™ˆğŸ™ˆğŸ™ˆ NO NO NO!! It is ok to eat these foods once in awhile with a balanced diet but you cannot just say 'It fits your macros, therefore you can have it'. People pick up these nuggets of information, use them and don't see results, why? Because they didn't use them properly and over induldged in these foods. It is essential to understand how you can have these things in moderation but you will only get that through a nutritionist. - Secondly, let's be straight here. If you are a normal person training 3 times a week, looking to lose weight and body fat, your diet DOES not need to be the same as an athletes training 5-6 times a week. For so many reasons. 1. Athletes require more carbs - it is essential fuel for sport. 2. Athletes body compositions are different so their BMR is higher and they need more food. 3. Their emphasis is on performance not aesthetics and the list goes on.

Obviously, I am both a nutritionist and an athlete so this area is hugely important to me. If you have any questions on this comment below or even drop me a DM I'm happy to help ğŸ¤—

caption:
Commitment ğŸ‘ŠğŸ‘ŠğŸ‘Š ğŸ‘‰You have goals. ğŸ‘‰You want to achieve them. ğŸ™ˆBut are you really commited to them? 
Now I don't mean dipping in and out. Some days giving all while others you slip up. I mean 100% commitment.

I mean eat, sleep and breath what you are doing. I mean long days just to get where you want to be. I mean not seeing your partner all weekend (or evenings for that matter). I mean missing out on social events. I mean saying no!!! Until you've done the above things. You are not fully commited. You are not truely sacrificing. And if you want something you've never had, you have to do something you've never done ğŸ‘Š

And there is no worse pain than doing everything you can possibly do, and still not come out on top. But that's just life. Nothing is linear. The road to success is hard, it's long and it's God damn bumpy. Sit back and enjoy the ride ğŸ‘Š

#football #youwinsomeyoulosemore #positivity #commitment #sacrifice #gaagirls

Training âœ”
Nutrition âœ”
Recovery âœ”
Sleep âœ”

Remember, training is important but it is only a TINY fraction of your time. While it's important to give it all while you're there the mjority of our time is spent recovering. Recovering includes nutrition and sleep ğŸ˜ªğŸ¥‘ğŸ¥ It also includes foam rolling and for me Ice baths. It's all dependent on your goals, your training frequency and the intensity of your training. @komplexfitness wrote a great post on recovery. caption:
Heart Rate and Resting Heart Rate

I put up a poll about this and a lot of you wrote to me so I said I'd try explain a little more.

Heart Rate is the speed of the heartbeat measured by the number of contractions of the heart per minute. This can vary according to the body's physical needs including absorbing oxygen and excreting carbon dioxide. A great example is comparing at rest to during physical activity, the demand for oxygen is much higher during exercise than at rest.

Resting heart rate can be affected by exercise, sleep, illness, stress, anxiety and the use of drugs. Normal ranges of RHR are 50-90BPM. Normally, the more cardiovascularly fit you are the lower your RHR. It may be below 60. The lowest ever was achieved by Daniel Green in 2014 with a reading of 26BPM.

Specific heart rate zones are required for specific goals with regard exercise i.e fat burning, cardio and peak.  Your max HR is 220- Age.

I now use this as one of my goals. As I said before my goals are no longer aesthetic based but performance. One of my goals was to get my RHR below 50 âœ”

caption:
The million dollar question I seem to be getting asked ALOT recently ğŸ™ˆğŸ™ˆğŸ™ˆ ğŸ‘‰Should women or kids be lifting weights?
There is a lot of crap out there on this topic. A lot of myths and some made up crap. You really would be suprised the amount of people I deal with on a daily basis who believe women 'should not be lifting weights' and 'lifting weights stunts your growth'. ğŸ‘‰ I'll deal with these 2 seperately. Kids/Teenagers can do resistance exercise. Bodyweight exercise is vitally important for gaining muscle mass, reducing body fat, mobility, bone strengthening. If you can successfully excute all bodyweight exercises, you're onto a winner. ğŸ‘‰ Is there an age you can start lifting weights? The research suggests that youths can lift weights as long as the reps are high and the weight is light. ğŸ‘‰ Resistance exercise is of VITAL importance to all ages and all genders. It can be in the form of bodyweight or weights but it is necessary for increasing fat free mass. The problem with anyone lifting weights is due to lack of information and incorrect technique. It WILL NOT make you masculine and if anything it emphasises your feminine features ğŸ‘ğŸ‘ğŸ‘ But get proper knowledge from a trainer. If you care enough about it, invest in it ğŸ˜

caption:
At the end of the day, all weight gain, weight maintenance, weight loss comes down to this single concept.

Annoyingly, you can gain weight from eating too much healthy foods if the calories are high enough and similarly you can lose weight from eating crap if the calories are low enough ğŸ˜£

But are all calories created equal?
ğŸ‘‰ This is opinion, not fact.
ğŸ‘‰ Whether you hit your macros, nail your calories or not, daily takeaways are not healthy in my eyes. Sure you may look good on the outside but the discomfort of digesting that food is not healthy and not good for you inside.
ğŸ‘‰ People become so OBSESSED with how they look on the outside they totally forget, it's whats on the inside that counts. No point having a sparkly, shiny car and the engine about to blow up. Our bodies are the same.

caption:
Morning all ğŸ¤—

So I'm going to try to increase my food posts as best as I can and my main aim is to educate you all on a healthier lifestyle ğŸ¤ğŸ‘Œ So I've said before that I don't count calories, never have probably never will ğŸ™ˆ I don't count macros because I have a fair idea what is in food, what I need more of and what I can do better on. I'm not shredded but instead am a healthy weight and most importantly I'm healthy inside and out ğŸ‘ŒğŸ‘Š Remember health is not always about aesthetics ğŸ‘ğŸ‘ğŸ‘ But I do have a brain and I use it wisely ğŸ˜‹ğŸ˜† Some of you will hate this, some of you will see the benefit. So I went to the cinema last night, and instead of getting cinema pop corn I opted for a lower calorie option. Propercorn is a fantastic substitute for cinema popcorn if weight loss is a goal. It comes in at just 88Cals compared to our 'SMALL' cinema popcorn at 200-300 Cals (and who ever buys small). I also brought water instead of a fizzy drink. 
Some of you will think for the love of God this is extreme. Others will understand. I don't always opt for the healthy option. I was the first one at Christmas head first in Celebrations but if you want to maintain a healthy lifestyle you need to make changes. Eating crap makes me feel like crap and so in turn I try not to do it. I try to find healthier alternatives that make me feel better but without restricting myself ğŸ¤—
